trend_summary: Across the time-series the corridor remains dominantly agricultural. Small villages in the centre and several junctions grow outward slightly, new farmsteads appear, and a few fields replace forest patches, but no large urban cores form. Transport lines are marginally upgraded. Overall land use stays rural with sparse, scattered construction.
notable_changes: Incremental outward growth of the main central village and two smaller hamlets.
New or widened road segments cutting diagonally through the mid-section.
Forest blocks in the northern and southern ends cleared and converted to cropland.
Emergence of several light-colored farm buildings and storage yards within fields.
Slight increase in field regularity, indicating agricultural intensification.
